definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  L-tryptophan + pyruvate -eq- 3-(indol-3-yl)pyruvate + L-alanine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  L-glutamine + 2-oxoglutarate -eq- 2-oxoglutaramate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + phosphatidyl-N-dimethylethanolamine -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + phosphatidylcholine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-methylthiopropyl-glucosinolate -eq- 3-methylsulfinylpropyl-glucosinolate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  5-methylthiopropyl-glucosinolate -eq- 5-methylsulfinylpropyl-glucosinolate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-methylthiopropyl-glucosinolate -eq- 6-methylsulfinylpropyl-glucosinolate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  7-methylthiopropyl-glucosinolate -eq- 7-methylsulfinylpropyl-glucosinolate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  8-methylthiopropyl-glucosinolate -eq- 8-methylsulfinylpropyl-glucosinolate.
Catalysis of the conversion of a S-alkylthiohydroximate to a thiohydroximate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  indole-3-acetonitrile + H2O -eq- indole-3-acetamide.
The removal of a methyl group from one or more nucleotides within an DNA molecule.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the tail region of a myosin XI heavy chain.
Catalysis of the transfer of glucuronate to the xylan backbone of glucuronoxylan molecule.

Catalysis of the reaction -  a brassinosteroid + 3'-phosphoadenosine-5'-phosphosulfate -eq- sulfated brassinosteroid + adenosine-3',5'-diphosphate. This reaction is the transfer of a sulfate group to the hydroxyl group of a brassinosteroid acceptor, producing the sulfated brassinosteroid derivative.
Catalysis of the transfer of AMP, adenosine monophosphate, from one side of a membrane to the other.

Catalysis of the reaction -  jasmonate + an amino acid -eq- an amide-linked jasmonyl-amino acid conjugate. The substrates of this reaction include non-standard amino acids, such as ACC (1-aminocyclopropane-1-carboxylate).
Catalysis of the reaction -  pheophytin + H2O -eq- phytol + pheophorbide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-phenylalanine + 2-oxoglutarate -eq- phenylpyruvate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a hydroxyjasmonate + 3'-phosphoadenosine-5'-phosphosulfate -eq- a hydroxyjasmonate sulfate + adenosine-3',5'-diphosphate.
Catalysis of the conversion of a fatty acid to an alpha-hydroxylated fatty acid. A hydroxyl group is added to the second carbon, counted from the carboxyl end, of a fatty acid chain.
Catalysis of the conversion of an alkane to a secondary alcohol.
Catalysis of the transfer of borate from the outside of a cell to the inside of the cell across a membrane.
Catalysis of the transfer of borate from the inside of the cell to the outside of the cell across a membrane.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-cysteine + H2O -eq- ammonia + pyruvate + hydrogen sulfide + H+.
Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate of translation as a result of increase in sucrose level.

label.value: S-adenosyl-L-methionine - benzoic acid carboxyl methyl transferase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  benzoate + S-adenosyl-L-methionine -eq- methylbenzoate + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the transfer of auxins from one side of the membrane to the other. Auxins are plant hormones that regulate aspects of plant growth.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of xyloglucan side chains so as to remove unsubstituted D-xylose residues attached to the glucose located at the non-reducing terminus.

An epigenetic RNA-based gene silencing process first elucidated in plants whereby 24-nt small interfering RNAs (siRNAs) guide DNA methyltransferases to the siRNA-generating genomic loci and other loci that are homologous to the siRNAs for de novo DNA methylation. In general this process consists of three phases -  biogenesis of siRNAs, scaffold RNA production, and the formation of the guiding complex that recruits de novo DNA methyltransferases to the target loci.
A complex, symbiont-induced host-derived organelle that is comprised of multiple protein and lipid domains.
A projection from a cell or tissue that penetrates the host's cell wall and invaginates the host cell membrane.
The space between the symbiont plasma membrane and the extrahaustorial membrane of the host.
The membrane surrounding the symbiont haustorium during symbiosis, derived from the host plasma membrane.
A host-derived membrane surrounding the symbiont invasive hypha during symbiosis.
The space between the symbiont plasma membrane and the extra-invasive hyphal membrane.
Highly branched symbiont haustoria within host root cortex cells, responsible for nutrient exchange.
A host-derived membrane surrounding the symbiont arbuscule during symbiosis.

label.value: voltage-gated sodium channel activity involved in cardiac muscle cell action potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a sodium ion by a voltage-gated channel through the plasma membrane of a cardiac muscle cell contributing to the depolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: voltage-gated calcium channel activity involved in cardiac muscle cell action potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a voltage-gated channel across the plasma membrane of a cardiac muscle cell that contributes to the depolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: voltage-gated potassium channel activity involved in cardiac muscle cell action potential repolarization

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a potassium ion by a voltage-gated channel through the plasma membrane of a cardiac muscle cell contributing to the repolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: gap junction channel activity involved in SA node cell-atrial cardiac muscle cell electrical coupling

definition.value: A wide pore channel activity that enables a direct cytoplasmic connection from an SA node cell to an atrial cardiomyocyte. The gap junction passes electrical signals between the cells contributing to cardiac conduction.

label.value: sodium - potassium-exchanging ATPase activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + Na+(in) + K+(out) -eq- ADP + phosphate + Na+(out) + K+(in), that contributes to regulating the membrane potential of a cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: calcium - sodium antiporter activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  Ca2+(in) + Na+(out) -eq- Ca2+(out) + Na+(in), which contributes to regulating the membrane potential of a cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: calcium-transporting ATPase activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a cardiac muscle cell plasma membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + Ca2+(cis) -eq- ADP + phosphate + Ca2+(trans). The transfer contributes to the regulation of the plasma membrane potential.

label.value: sodium - proton antiporter activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a cardiac muscle cell membrane to the other according to the reaction -  Na+(out) + H+(in) -eq- Na+(in) + H+(out). This transfer contributes to the regulation of the cardiac muscle cell plasma membrane potential.

label.value: voltage-gated potassium channel activity involved in SA node cell action potential depolarization

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a sodium ion by a voltage-gated channel through the plasma membrane of an SA node cardiac muscle cell contributing to the depolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: voltage-gated calcium channel activity involved in AV node cell action potential

definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a voltage-gated channel across the plasma membrane of an AV node cardiac muscle cell that contributes to the depolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.
